WRITING.TITLE: I'm angry with the way my body looks and I take it out on my skin. My best friend gets uncomfortable when I ask her for help (and I don't blame her) so I decided maybe I'll try here.

WRITING.TEXT: -There's an app called Calm Harm that I used for a bit...really helped. -use a washable marker and draw a butterfly (or another animal you like) on your skin where you feel urged to harm yourself. Don't scrub it off, let it fade away naturally. -get up and take a walk or go on a run. The exercise is healthy and the fresh air will make you feel better. It may seem cheesy or stupid, but this has helped me quite a bit. If you feel urges a lot, you'll find yourself in very good shape, which is always a plus. You're beautiful, inside and out.
